Three people were injured – one of them seriously – when the vehicle they were travelling in veered off the road and crashed into a wall along Old Ottery Road in Ottery late on Saturday afternoon, according to paramedics. Paramedics from ER24, Western Cape Fire and Rescue Services and Life Healthcare attended the crash scene, where they found three men inside the car, ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. "The driver and rear passenger sustained moderate injuries. They were treated on the crash scene, and transported to Victoria Hospital for further care. "The front passenger sustained serious injuries and had to be freed from the vehicle by the fire department," Vermaak added. The cause of the Ottery crash was not yet known, according to Vermaak. African News Agency  